# TALOME — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Talome is an AI-first, open-source home server management platform.
Beautiful shadcn/ui dashboard + AI chat management + Docker container orchestration.

## Architecture
- Monorepo: pnpm workspaces + Turborepo
- apps/dashboard: Next.js 15 + React 19 + shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS 4
- apps/core: Hono server + Vercel AI SDK + SQLite (Drizzle ORM)
- packages/types: Shared TypeScript types

## Tech Stack & Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode everywhere
- Next.js App Router (no Pages Router)
- Server Components by default, 'use client' only when needed
- shadcn/ui for all UI components — never install alternative component libs
- Hugeicons (@hugeicons/react + @hugeicons/core-free-icons) for icons — NOT Lucide
  - Use HugeiconsIcon wrapper: <HugeiconsIcon icon={Home01Icon} size={20} />
  - lucide-react only exists as peer dep for shadcn internals, never import it directly
- Tailwind CSS 4 with CSS variables for theming (dark/light)
- All theming in globals.css — no inline styles, no per-component color overrides
- Vercel AI SDK for all LLM interactions (streamText, tool)
- Hono for the backend API
- Drizzle ORM + better-sqlite3 for persistence
- Zod for all runtime validation and tool parameter schemas
- Error handling: use Result types, never throw in library code
- Naming: kebab-case files, PascalCase components, camelCase functions
- Exports: named exports only, no default exports (except Next.js pages)

## Johnny Ive Design Rules
- Radical reduction: if it doesn't serve the user's task, remove it
- Breathing space: p-6 minimum on content areas, gap-6 between cards
- Honest materials: no decorative gradients, no fake shadows
- One primary action per view
- Every animation < 200ms, ease-out, no bounce, no spring overshoot
- Typography: text-sm, text-base, text-lg, text-2xl only. Weight 400/500 only.
- Dark mode is the default

## Security Rules
- NEVER use eval() or execute arbitrary code
- NEVER expose Docker socket directly to the frontend
- All API routes validate input with Zod
- API keys stored in .env, never committed
- CORS restricted to dashboard origin only
